  "text": "Once upon a matchday — it was the quarter-final, on the 12th of July 2026 — two teams walked out under the soft evening lights. Argentina outlasted Switzerland in extra time to set up a blockbuster semi-final with England. The champions were made to work deep into extra time by a Swiss side riding the high of their shootout heroics.\n\nIn the 10th minute, Alexis Mac Allister sent the ball gently home, and the score whispered 1–0. In the 68th minute, Dan Ndoye sent the ball gently home, and the score whispered 1–1. In the 114th minute, Julián Álvarez sent the ball gently home, and the score whispered 2–1. In the 121st minute, Lautaro Martínez sent the ball gently home, and the score whispered 3–1.\n\nAlexis Mac Allister headed in a Messi corner early, twice left unmarked and punishing it the second time. Dan Ndoye levelled with a tight-angle finish after a neat one-two, and Switzerland dug in for extra time. Then Julián Álvarez unleashed a wonderful strike from distance in the 112th minute, and Lautaro Martínez added late gloss to seal it. Argentina keep finding another gear when the tie demands it — the mark of a team that knows how to win these.\n\nAnd so the story ended Argentina 3–1 Switzerland. Argentina carried on their long journey, and Switzerland lay down to rest. Every goal in this tale is a true one — kept safe and provable on the blockchain by TxLINE — so you can close your eyes knowing not a single fact was ever made up. Sleep well, and goodnight.",
